    {
      "id": "sensor-gate-dedup-pattern",
      "topics": [],
      "content": "All well-designed sensors follow Gate → Dedup → Create pattern:\n1. Interval gate via `claimSensorRun(name, intervalMinutes)`\n2. State dedup via hook-state file or task existence check\n3. Task creation only after both gates pass\n\nVerify completion in DB (`completedTaskCountForSource()`), not task creation.\nCreation-time marking blocks retries permanently.",
      "source": "arc",
      "created": "2026-03-01",
      "expires": "2026-09-01"
    },
    {
      "id": "sentinel-file-pattern",
      "topics": [],
      "content": "On capability outage (402, CreditsDepleted, API ban), write a sentinel file\n(e.g. `db/x-credits-depleted.json`) and gate all downstream sensors/callers.\nCheck sentinel before runtime failure. Without a gate, sensors cascade new\nfailures continuously. Remove sentinel when capability restored.",
      "source": "arc",
      "created": "2026-03-01",
      "expires": "2026-09-01"
    },
    {
      "id": "credential-safety",
      "topics": [],
      "content": "Never pass secrets via command-line flags — they leak to process history.\nUse env vars, stdin, or credential store APIs. `getCredential()` returns\nPromises — always `await`. Validate credentials at health-check time,\nnot on first API call. Dual-endpoint APIs may use different auth headers\nper endpoint class — document both in SKILL.md.",
      "source": "arc",
      "created": "2026-03-01"
    }
  ]
